      "content": "The Maillard reaction is a complex chemical process that occurs when amino acids and reducing sugars react under heat, giving food its delicious brown color and savory flavors. It's distinct from caramelization, which is simply the browning of sugar alone. Generally, this reaction begins to occur significantly around $285^\\circ\\mathrm{F}$ ($140^\\circ\\mathrm{C}$) and speeds up as the temperature increases.",
